Single-minded Unity of Korea Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 10 (KCNA) -- A seminar, a lecture and a reading session took place in Sofia, Kampala and Kinshasa between March 31 and April 5 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun and the 13th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK. 
 The first secretary of the Sofia City Committee of the Bulgarian Communist Party who is member of the Party Central Committee in a report at the seminar highly praised President Kim Il Sung for founding the immortal Juche idea and performing great exploits for the Korean revolution and the cause of global independence with his energetic leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il who has developed in depth the idea of Songun laid down by Kim Il Sung, the father of socialist Korea, is the iron-willed commander who is defending socialism and reliably protecting the security of the country and the people with the might of Songun, the reporter added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the African Regional Committee of Friendship and Solidarity with the Korean People in a lecture titled "Songun politics and single-minded unity of Korea" said that the Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il has further strengthened the single-minded unity of the army and the people. Invincible is Korea where the leader, the army and the people form the community of destiny, he stressed.
 The chairman of the Group for the Study of Kim Jong Il Juche Idea of Democratic Congo said at the reading session that thanks to Kim Jong Il, the revolutionary ideas of Kim Il Sung are shining as the banner of eternal victory of the Korean revolution, the guiding idea of humankind and Korea is demonstrating its might as a powerful state. He expressed his determination to make positive efforts to intensify the study and dissemination of the Juche idea in the future, too.

Events Held to Mark Kim Jong Il's Election as NDC Chairman 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 10 (KCNA) -- Events were held on April 9 to mark the 13th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission.
 Dancing parties of youth and students in Pyongyang were held in different parts of the city including plazas of the Tower of the Juche Idea, the Monument to Party Founding and Pyongyang Indoor Stadium. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were replete with the joy and happiness of holding Kim Jong Il, son of guerrillas and peerless commander of Songun, in high esteem as the supreme leader of the revolution. They danced to the tune of such songs as "Confetti of Best Wishes," "Let's Sing of Our Pride in Being under the Guidance of the General", "Our General Is Best", "Thunder on Jong Il Peak", and "Let's Sing of General Dear to People".
 Dancing parties of youth and students were also held in different provincial seats, cities and counties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A performance was given by the central youth art squad at the Central Youth Hall.
 The performers truthfully represented the pride and happiness of being blessed with the illustrious leaders generation after generation in such colorful numbers as chorus and dance "Glory to General Kim Jong Il", male solo "The General Is Son of Guerillas", dance "Very Ambitious Girls" and poem and chorus "All Servicepersons and People Will Become Human Bullets and Bombs". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A dancing party of members of the Korean Democratic Women's Union was also held at the plaza of the Tower of the Juche Idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its participants danced to the tune of such songs as "Fortune of Korea", "Song of Three Prides", "Inspired by the General, Who Is a Crack Shot, We Never Miss Targets," "Let's Advance Faster for Higher Goal" representing their firm faith and will to uphold Kim Jong Il with loyalty.

Pro-U.S. Forces' Treachery Flailed in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 10 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification reportedly made public a statement on April 5 denouncing the Grand National Party and the conservative media for zealously supporting the U.S. in its moves for a war against the north.
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Defence Ministry complained to the police all the participants in the demonstration staged in protest against the joint landing exercises on the charge of "disturbing the performance of special duty." On April 4 GNP Representative Pak Kun Hye addressing its "Supreme Committee" demanded the "government" take a strong action against the participants in the demonstration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The conservative media including Chosun Ilbo, chiming in with her outcry, released only misinformation about the demonstration, falsifying the truth that the recent joint military exercises were aimed at invading the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-U.S., anti-war action of the participants in the demonstration was a patriotic resistance reflecting the desire for national unity and reunification, the statement noted, strongly demanding the ministry immediately withdraw the charge brought against them.

24th April Spring Friendship Art Festival Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 10 (KCNA) -- The 24th April Spring Friendship Art Festival was opened in Pyongyang on Monday.
 As dusk fell, the festively decorated Pyongyang Grand Theatre, the venue of its inaugural ceremony, and streets adjacent to it were brightly lit. 
 Flags of the festival were seen fluttering and its posters displayed at the plaza of the theatre. There a women's brass band played merry music with attracting rhythms while dancers in graceful national costumes presented beautiful dances and acrobats colorful numbers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the opening ceremony were Vice-President of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly Yang Hyong Sop, Minister of Culture Kim Jin Song who is chairman of the organizing committee of the festival and other officials concerned, working people and artistes in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present were foreign artistes and overseas Korean artistes, the Chinese government cultural delegation and other foreign delegations and delegates participating in the festival, honorary guests of the festival, foreign diplomatic envoys and embassy officials here and foreign guests and overseas Koreans staying in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jin Song in an opening address said that it is the pleasure of the Korean people and the pride of humankind to have such a friendly stage of world-level in Pyongyang as the April Spring Friendship Art Festival which brought together the men of culture and arts from different parts of the world aspiring after genuine arts so that they might have the opportunity to loudly sing of the songs of independence, peace and friendship and enrich human culture and arts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival would provide its participants with chances to present diverse and peculiar programs representing the shining achievements made by various countries, nations and regions of the world in the cultural development and thus enrich genuine human civilization and emotion and give strong impetus to the development of human culture, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the belief that the festival would encourage the development of human culture and the just cause of the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Oleg Oleinik, president of the Russian International Charity Fund "Protectors of Arts for the Century" who is heading its delegation, in a congratulatory speech said that the Korean people, guided by the immortal Juche idea founded by President Kim Il Sung, the eternal sun of Korea, are fully determined to defend the sovereignty of the country and apply the idea of independence, peace and friendship, the centuries-old desire of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last instructions of Kim Il Sung, the father of socialist Korea and the great man of the century, are being successfully carried out under the wise leadership of 
Kim Jong Il and the feats performed by Kim Il Sung are highly appreciated by the world, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that participating in the festival he once again keenly realized the invincible might displayed by the Korean people under the leadership of Kim Jong Il.
 Foreign and Korean artistes hoisted the flag of the festival amid the playing of the song "Brilliant Country" in the theatre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The inaugural ceremony was followed by a performance given by Korean artistes.

Kim Il Sung's Immortal Exploits in Environmental Protection
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 10 (KCNA) -- Twenty years have passed since President Kim Il Sung made public the famous work "On Improving the Work of Protecting the Environment" on April 10, Juche75(1986), the day following the adoption of the "Law on Environmental Protection of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea".
 The President, in his work, advanced detailed tasks and ways for improving the work of protecting the environment.
 The Korean people take this opportunity to look back on the efforts the President, with an ardent patriotism, had bent to provide them with better living environment.
 After the country's liberation he paid a deep attention to the work of restoring the destroyed environment and improving people's working and living conditions. He saw to it to take positive steps for protecting the health of workers and residents from poisonous gas and harmful labor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In those days when even one ton of steel was badly needed for the building of a new country, he said that no matter how valuable steel was, it could not be bartered for the lives of workers. And he determinedly instructed officials to blast away primitive furnaces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had always directed the primary attention to the environmental protection in building even a dwelling house or a factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il, true to far-reaching plan of the President, saw to it that the government was deeply concerned for the health of the people and the protection of environment and the content of the Law on Environmental Protection was further elaborated in line with the developing realities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK, true to the intention of the peerlessly great men, is directing much effort to the land construction and launching a campaign for greening the whole country as part of the work, thus constantly improving environment.

Colorfully Decorated Flower Festival Venue
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 10 (KCNA) -- The 8th Kimilsungia Festival will take place in the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition Hall in Pyongyang from April 13 to 20.
 The festival venue is now being decorated to suit festival theme "Eternal Spring Holiday of Humankind". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the exhibition stands are being arranged with electric photo boards reflecting images of the three generals of Mt. Paektu as the center. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The backgrounds of the stands to be arranged by military organs, ministries, national institutions and many other units are adorned mainly with flowers.
 The stands are designed to make Kimilsungia, the immortal flower, more conspicuous in every way and to depict the historical native home in Mangyongdae and others with rare flowers and plants, thus stirring up the festival atmosphere replete with boundless reverence for President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The inside of the festival venue is bedecked with sorts of flowers including azaleas and apricot flowers blooming early in spring and various decorative facilities.
 The annual festival has developed year by year in formative and artistic way, unfolding beautiful scenes beyond description.
